I use Quarto’s repo to get ideas for my website and how to code it up. Recently I was attempting to make buttons and found an example on the repo. I was able to make two simple buttons that did function as intended to other pages in the website, but they looked totally different than what I was expecting. Later I asked Brother Hathaway what the code is that is used to make the code, he informed me that it is CSS. Now I’m excited to learn more about CSS!
There’s many things that I want to learn about and Quarto will serve as my notepad. Just recently thanks to Sir. Stack “CTR+C CTR+P” Overflow, I learned how to embed PDF’s into my QMD file. Here’s an example using the Forcats cheatsheet:

<div id="quarto-navigation-envelope" class="hidden">
